<br>
But I'm not so sure it is the greatest soloing pet at your level.  And besides, you can give whips to the fire pet too.<br>
 <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=4796"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Baron Zacatac Soulwanderer</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jarlo99>Jarlo99</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 38<br> <font color=#333333>(2/19/03 5:15:20 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=988.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: pre-51 air pet?</span><hr size=1> My 49 (and now 53) air pet makes casting mobs a joke.  The wizards in Neriak (lvl 40ish) can hardly get a spell off with the pet stunning every 9 seconds or so.  It is very helpful in groups for interrupting spells and damage mitigation.  Heck my 49 air pet was interrupting clerics in hate this weekend <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
